<h2 id="30">3. Linking template containers</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Proceed as follows to set up container links:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Plugins » Plugin set overview</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the plugin set you want to edit.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the plugin <strong>Mollie</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Container links</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select one or more containers in which the previously selected content is to be displayed.<br>
→ Pay attention to the information provided in <a href="#table-mollie-template-container">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The content is linked to the containers.</p>
</li>
